qas.question: What is the most famous immune system disease?
What kind of disease is AIDS?
Which types of cells are suppressed by AIDS?

answers.text: CD4+ ("helper") T cells, dendritic cells and macrophages

qas.question: What virus specifically suppresses those cells?

context: The most well-known disease that affects the immune system itself is <a0_0>AIDS<a0_0/>, <a1_0>an immunodeficiency<a1_0/> characterized by the suppression of <a2_0>CD4+ ("helper") T cells, dendritic cells and macrophages<a2_0/> by the <a3_0>Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV)<a3_0/>.
